record.notes:
&quot;the difference between clinical/biologic validity and clinical utility&quot;

&quot;Clinical utility. Clinical utility requires that an assay
with analytic and clinical validity be shown to be useful in improving patient outcomes to the extent that the patient’s care should differ than if the marker results were not available.&quot;

&quot;Determination of clinical utility requires judgment, on the part of the caregiver, the patient, and society, in regard to the relative benefits comapred with the risks and costs of the therapeutic plan under consideration&quot;

&quot;adjuvant endocrine therapy decreases relapse in only ap-proximately one-half of ER-positive patients who are des-tined to experience recurrence. ER does, though, strongly
identify patients who will not benefit.&quot;

“a bad tumor marker is as bad as a bad drug.”

